This paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence techniques, specifically neural networks and support vector machines, for predicting militarised conflict. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the cs.AI sub-category. Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms for prediction suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also discusses the sensitivity analysis of the models, which could place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. The topic of conflict management could also place it in the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of conflict on society, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category.
